{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899604903,"sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdd7316001KQU0SLUKKOLDJJ","messageID":"msg_d7bdd641c001Opu8y7C8PcjL9A","sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4b73e3ca73864c4aa05037a7e6317e76","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Module: `sdk-python/tests`\n6: Language: Python\n7: Size: M\n8: Task: Add comprehensive unit tests for AgentCube Python SDK components\n9: \n10: ## Base Specs\n11: \n12: - `python-sdk/design.md` — Package layout, client APIs, configuration, HTTP contracts\n13: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — SDK requirements with acceptance scenarios\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: Unit tests for ControlPlaneClient\n18: \n19: #### SCENARIO-001: Create session success\n20: ```gherkin\n21: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with base_url=\"http://wm-mock\" and auth_token=\"test-token\"\n22: WHEN create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\", metadata=None, ttl=1800) is called\n23: AND the mock server returns {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n24: THEN the HTTP request should be POST to \"/v1/code-interpreter\"\n25: AND the request body should contain {\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\",\"ttl\":1800,\"metadata\":null}\n26: AND the method should return \"session-123\"\n27: ```\n28: \n29: #### SCENARIO-002: Create session missing sessionId in response\n30: ```gherkin\n31: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\n32: WHEN create_session is called and the mock returns {\"data\": {}}\n33: THEN ValueError should be raised with message containing \"sessionId\"\n34: ```\n35: \n36: #### SCENARIO-003: Delete session with 404 response\n37: ```gherkin\n38: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\n39: WHEN delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\") is called and the server returns 404\n40: THEN the method should return True\n41: ```\n42: \n43: #### SCENARIO-004: Delete session with error response\n44: ```gherkin\n45: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\n46: WHEN delete_session(\"session-123\") is called and the server returns 500\n47: THEN the error should be logged\n48: AND the method should return False\n49: ```\n50: \n51: #### SCENARIO-005: Resolve workload manager URL from argument\n52: ```gherkin\n53: GIVEN workload_manager_url=\"http://custom-wm\" argument\n54: AND WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable set to \"http://env-wm\"\n55: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n56: THEN base_url should be \"http://custom-wm\"\n57: ```\n58: \n59: #### SCENARIO-006: Resolve workload manager URL from environment\n60: ```gherkin\n61: GIVEN no workload_manager_url argument\n62: AND WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://env-wm\" environment variable set\n63: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n64: THEN base_url should be \"http://env-wm\"\n65: ```\n66: \n67: #### SCENARIO-007: Resolve auth token from file\n68: ```gherkin\n69: GIVEN no auth_token argument\n70: AND SA token file contains \"service-account-token\\n\"\n71: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n72: THEN Authorization header should be set to \"Bearer service-account-token\"\n73: ```\n74: \n75: #### SCENARIO-008: Close closes HTTP session\n76: ```gherkin\n77: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with an active HTTP session\n78: WHEN close is called\n79: THEN the HTTP session should be closed\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### REQ-002: Unit tests for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n85: \n86: #### SCENARIO-009: Execute command success\n87: ```gherkin\n88: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n89: AND a mocked HTTP session\n90: WHEN execute_command(\"echo hello\") is called\n91: AND the mock returns {\"stdout\":\"hello\\n\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"exitCode\":0}\n92: THEN the request should POST to \"api/execute\"\n93: AND the request body should be {\"command\":[\"echo\",\"hello\"],\"timeout\":\"122.0s\"}\n94: AND the method should return the stdout value\n95: ```\n96: \n97: #### SCENARIO-010: Execute command with list command\n98: ```gherkin\n99: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n100: WHEN execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\"]) is called\n101: AND the mock returns successful response\n102: THEN the request body command should be [\"ls\",\"-la\"]\n103: ```\n104: \n105: #### SCENARIO-011: Execute command non-zero exit raises error\n106: ```gherkin\n107: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n108: WHEN execute_command(\"exit 1\") is called\n109: AND the mock returns {\"stdout\":\"\",\"stderr\":\"error\",\"exitCode\":1}\n110: THEN CommandExecutionError should be raised with exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=[\"exit\",\"1\"]\n111: ```\n112: \n113: #### SCENARIO-012: Execute command timeout override\n114: ```gherkin\n115: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\n116: WHEN execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0) is called\n117: THEN the request body should contain timeout=\"32.0s\"\n118: ```\n119: \n120: #### SCENARIO-013: Execute command default timeout\n121: ```gherkin\n122: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\n123: WHEN execute_command(\"echo test\", timeout=None) is called\n124: THEN the request body should contain timeout=\"122.0s\"\n125: ```\n126: \n127: #### SCENARIO-014: Run code Python writes file and executes\n128: ```gherkin\n129: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with mocked methods\n130: WHEN run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\") is called\n131: THEN write_file should be called with a .py file containing the code\n132: AND execute_command should be called with \"python3 <filename>\"\n133: ```\n134: \n135: #### SCENARIO-015: Write file with base64 encoding\n136: ```gherkin\n137: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n138: WHEN write_file(\"hello world\", \"/tmp/test.txt\") is called\n139: THEN the request body should contain base64-encoded content\n140: AND the path should be \"/tmp/test.txt\"\n141: AND mode should be \"0644\"\n142: ```\n143: \n144: #### SCENARIO-016: Upload file multipart\n145: ```gherkin\n146: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n147: AND a local file \"/local/file.txt\"\n148: WHEN upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/file.txt\") is called\n149: THEN the request should be multipart POST\n150: AND the data should contain path=\"/remote/file.txt\" and mode=\"0644\"\n151: AND session header should be set\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### SCENARIO-017: Download file streams response\n155: ```gherkin\n156: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n157: WHEN download_file(\"/tmp/test.txt\", \"/local/test.txt\") is called\n158: AND the mock returns streaming response\n159: THEN the request should be GET \"api/files/tmp/test.txt\"\n160: AND the response content should be written to local file\n161: AND stream=True should be used\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### SCENARIO-018: List files returns JSON\n165: ```gherkin\n166: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n167: WHEN list_files(\"/tmp\") is called\n168: AND the mock returns [{\"name\":\"test.txt\",\"size\":11}]\n169: THEN the request should be GET \"api/files?path=/tmp\"\n170: AND the method should return the parsed JSON\n171: ```\n172: \n173: #### SCENARIO-019: Base URL construction from router URL\n174: ```gherkin\n175: GIVEN router_url=\"http://router\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"test-ci\"\n176: AND base_url is not provided\n177: WHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n178: THEN base_url should be \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test-ci/invocations/\"\n179: ```\n180: \n181: #### SCENARIO-020: Base URL uses provided value\n182: ```gherkin\n183: GIVEN base_url=\"http://custom-base\" is provided\n184: WHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n185: THEN base_url should be \"http://custom-base\"\n186: ```\n187: \n188: #### SCENARIO-021: Session header included in requests\n189: ```gherkin\n190: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\n191: WHEN any _request method is called\n192: THEN the request should include header \"x-agentcube-session-id: test-session\"\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### REQ-003: Unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n198: \n199: #### SCENARIO-022: Bootstrap session ID success\n200: ```gherkin\n201: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with router_url=\"http://router\"\n202: AND namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n203: WHEN bootstrap_session_id() is called\n204: AND the GET request returns header \"x-agentcube-session-id: session-456\"\n205: THEN the GET request should go to the correct URL\n206: AND the method should return \"session-456\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: #### SCENARIO-023: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n210: ```gherkin\n211: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient configured for a valid agent\n212: WHEN bootstrap_session_id() is called\n213: AND the response lacks the session header\n214: THEN ValueError should be raised with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n215: ```\n216: \n217: #### SCENARIO-024: Invoke without session ID raises error\n218: ```gherkin\n219: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with session_id=None or falsy\n220: WHEN invoke(\"session-id\", {\"message\": \"test\"}) is called with empty session_id\n221: THEN ValueError should be raised with message \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n222: ```\n223: \n224: #### SCENARIO-025: Invoke success\n225: ```gherkin\n226: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\n227: WHEN invoke(\"active-session\", {\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=None) is called\n228: AND the mock returns successful response\n229: THEN the request should POST to base_url\n230: AND the request should include session header and JSON payload\n231: AND timeout should be (connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n232: ```\n233: \n234: #### SCENARIO-026: Invoke with timeout override\n235: ```gherkin\n236: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\n237: WHEN invoke(\"session-id\", {\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60.0) is called\n238: THEN the request timeout should be (connect_timeout, 60.0)\n239: ```\n240: \n241: #### SCENARIO-027: Base URL construction\n242: ```gherkin\n243: GIVEN router_url=\"http://router\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n244: WHEN AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n245: THEN base_url should be \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n246: ```\n247: \n248: #### SCENARIO-028: SESSION_HEADER constant\n249: ```gherkin\n250: GIVEN the AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient class\n251: WHEN the SESSION_HEADER class constant is accessed\n252: THEN it should be \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ### REQ-004: Unit tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n258: \n259: #### SCENARIO-029: Initialize with provided session_id\n260: ```gherkin\n261: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with session_id=\"existing-session\"\n262: AND router_url=\"http://router\"\n263: WHEN the client is initialized\n264: THEN create_session should NOT be called\n265: AND _init_data_plane should be called with session_id=\"existing-session\"\n266: ```\n267: \n268: #### SCENARIO-030: Initialize without session_id creates new session\n269: ```gherkin\n270: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient without session_id\n271: AND workload_manager_url=\"http://wm\", router_url=\"http://router\"\n272: WHEN the client is initialized\n273: AND create_session returns \"new-session-id\"\n274: THEN _init_data_plane should be called with session_id=\"new-session-id\"\n275: ```\n276: \n277: #### SCENARIO-031: Data plane init failure after session create\n278: ```gherkin\n279: GIVEN session_id was not provided\n280: AND create_session succeeds returning \"session-123\"\n281: AND _init_data_plane raises an exception\n282: WHEN the client is initialized\n283: THEN a warning should be logged\n284: AND delete_session(\"session-123\") should be called\n285: AND session_id should be set to None\n286: AND the exception should be re-raised\n287: ```\n288: \n289: #### SCENARIO-032: Router URL required\n290: ```gherkin\n291: GIVEN neither router_url argument nor ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\n292: WHEN CodeInterpreterClient.__init__ is called\n293: THEN ValueError should be raised with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n294: ```\n295: \n296: #### SCENARIO-033: Context manager normal exit\n297: ```gherkin\n298: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient used as a context manager\n299: AND session_id was set\n300: WHEN the context block exits without exception\n301: THEN __exit__ should call stop()\n302: AND stop should close data plane client\n303: AND stop should call delete_session if session_id is set\n304: AND stop should close control plane HTTP session\n305: ```\n306: \n307: #### SCENARIO-034: Context manager exception exit\n308: ```gherkin\n309: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient used as a context manager\n310: AND an exception occurs within the context block\n311: WHEN the context block exits\n312: THEN __exit__ should call stop() for cleanup\n313: AND the exception should be re-raised\n314: ```\n315: \n316: #### SCENARIO-035: Execute command delegates to data plane\n317: ```gherkin\n318: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n319: WHEN execute_command(\"echo test\") is called\n320: THEN the data plane client's execute_command should be called with the same arguments\n321: ```\n322: \n323: #### SCENARIO-036: Run code delegates to data plane\n324: ```gherkin\n325: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n326: WHEN run_code(\"python\", \"print('test')\") is called\n327: THEN the data plane client's run_code should be called with the same arguments\n328: ```\n329: \n330: #### SCENARIO-037: Write file delegates to data plane\n331: ```gherkin\n332: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n333: WHEN write_file(\"content\", \"/path/file.txt\") is called\n334: THEN the data plane client's write_file should be called with the same arguments\n335: ```\n336: \n337: #### SCENARIO-038: Upload file delegates to data plane\n338: ```gherkin\n339: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n340: WHEN upload_file(\"/local/file\", \"/remote/file\") is called\n341: THEN the data plane client's upload_file should be called with the same arguments\n342: ```\n343: \n344: #### SCENARIO-039: Download file delegates to data plane\n345: ```gherkin\n346: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n347: WHEN download_file(\"/remote/file\", \"/local/file\") is called\n348: THEN the data plane client's download_file should be called with the same arguments\n349: ```\n350: \n351: #### SCENARIO-040: List files delegates to data plane\n352: ```gherkin\n353: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n354: WHEN list_files(\"/path\") is called\n355: THEN the data plane client's list_files should be called with the same arguments\n356: ```\n357: \n358: #### SCENARIO-041: Stop closes data plane and deletes session\n359: ```gherkin\n360: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\n361: AND initialized data plane and control plane clients\n362: WHEN stop() is called\n363: THEN data plane client's close should be called\n364: AND control plane's delete_session(\"active-session\") should be called\n365: AND control plane's close should be called\n366: ```\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ### REQ-005: Unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n371: \n372: #### SCENARIO-042: Initialize with provided session_id\n373: ```gherkin\n374: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n375: AND session_id=\"existing-session\"\n376: AND router_url=\"http://router\"\n377: WHEN the client is initialized\n378: THEN bootstrap_session_id should NOT be called\n379: AND the session_id should be \"existing-session\"\n380: ```\n381: \n382: #### SCENARIO-043: Initialize without session_id bootstraps\n383: ```gherkin\n384: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n385: AND no session_id provided\n386: AND router_url=\"http://router\"\n387: WHEN the client is initialized\n388: AND bootstrap_session_id returns \"bootstrapped-session\"\n389: THEN the session_id should be \"bootstrapped-session\"\n390: ```\n391: \n392: #### SCENARIO-044: Context manager normal exit\n393: ```gherkin\n394: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient used as a context manager\n395: WHEN the context block exits without exception\n396: THEN __exit__ should call close()\n397: AND close should close the underlying requests.Session\n398: ```\n399: \n400: #### SCENARIO-045: Context manager exception exit\n401: ```gherkin\n402: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient used as a context manager\n403: AND an exception occurs within the context block\n404: WHEN the context block exits\n405: THEN __exit__ should call close()\n406: AND the exception should be re-raised\n407: ```\n408: \n409: #### SCENARIO-046: Invoke with valid session_id\n410: ```gherkin\n411: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\n412: WHEN invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=None) is called\n413: AND the data plane client returns a response\n414: THEN the data plane client's invoke should be called with session_id and payload\n415: AND the parsed response JSON should be returned\n416: ```\n417: \n418: #### SCENARIO-047: Invoke with timeout override\n419: ```gherkin\n420: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with default timeout=120\n421: WHEN invoke({\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60.0) is called\n422: THEN the data plane client's invoke should be called with timeout=60.0\n423: ```\n424: \n425: #### SCENARIO-048: Close closes HTTP session\n426: ```gherkin\n427: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with an active requests.Session\n428: WHEN close() is called\n429: THEN the requests.Session should be closed\n430: ```\n431: \n432: ---\n433: \n434: ### REQ-006: Unit tests for utility functions\n435: \n436: #### SCENARIO-049: read_token_from_file success\n437: ```gherkin\n438: GIVEN a temporary file containing \"test-token\\n\"\n439: WHEN read_token_from_file(file_path) is called\n440: THEN the function should return \"test-token\"\n441: AND whitespace should be stripped\n442: ```\n443: \n444: #### SCENARIO-050: read_token_from_file missing file\n445: ```gherkin\n446: GIVEN a non-existent file path\n447: WHEN read_token_from_file(file_path) is called\n448: THEN FileNotFoundError should be caught\n449: AND the function should return \"\"\n450: ```\n451: \n452: #### SCENARIO-051: create_session configures HTTPAdapter\n453: ```gherkin\n454: GIVEN pool_connections=5 and pool_maxsize=10\n455: WHEN create_session is called\n456: THEN HTTPAdapter should be mounted for \"http://\"\n457: AND HTTPAdapter should be mounted for \"https://\"\n458: AND pool_connections should be 5\n459: AND pool_maxsize should be 10\n460: ```\n461: \n462: #### SCENARIO-052: get_logger returns configured logger\n463: ```gherkin\n464: GIVEN name=\"test-logger\" and level=logging.DEBUG\n465: WHEN get_logger(name, level) is called\n466: THEN the returned logger should have name \"test-logger\"\n467: AND the logger should have level logging.DEBUG\n468: ```\n469: \n470: #### SCENARIO-053: get_logger with string level\n471: ```gherkin\n472: GIVEN name=\"test-logger\" and level=\"INFO\"\n473: WHEN get_logger(name, level) is called\n474: THEN the returned logger should have level logging.INFO\n475: ```\n476: \n477: ---\n478: \n479: ### REQ-007: Unit tests for exception hierarchy\n480: \n481: #### SCENARIO-054: CommandExecutionError attributes\n482: ```gherkin\n483: GIVEN exit_code=1, stderr=\"command failed\", command=[\"test\", \"cmd\"]\n484: WHEN CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command) is instantiated\n485: THEN error.exit_code should be 1\n486: AND error.stderr should be \"command failed\"\n487: AND error.command should be [\"test\", \"cmd\"]\n488: AND error message should contain \"exit 1\"\n489: ```\n490: \n491: #### SCENARIO-055: AgentCubeError is base exception\n492: ```gherkin\n493: GIVEN the AgentCubeError class\n494: WHEN an instance is created\n495: THEN it should be a subclass of Exception\n496: ```\n497: \n498: #### SCENARIO-056: CommandExecutionError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n499: ```gherkin\n500: GIVEN the CommandExecutionError class\n501: WHEN isinstance is checked\n502: THEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n503: ```\n504: \n505: #### SCENARIO-057: SessionError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n506: ```gherkin\n507: GIVEN the SessionError class\n508: WHEN isinstance is checked\n509: THEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n510: ```\n511: \n512: #### SCENARIO-058: DataPlaneError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n513: ```gherkin\n514: GIVEN the DataPlaneError class\n515: WHEN isinstance is checked\n516: THEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ### REQ-008: Unit tests for public API exports\n522: \n523: #### SCENARIO-059: Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n524: ```gherkin\n525: GIVEN the agentcube package\n526: WHEN \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\" is executed\n527: THEN CodeInterpreterClient should be imported successfully\n528: ```\n529: \n530: #### SCENARIO-060: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n531: ```gherkin\n532: GIVEN the agentcube package\n533: WHEN \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\" is executed\n534: THEN AgentRuntimeClient should be imported successfully\n535: ```\n536: \n537: #### SCENARIO-061: Root __all__ contains only public exports\n538: ```gherkin\n539: GIVEN the agentcube package\n540: WHEN __all__ is inspected\n541: THEN it should contain [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n542: AND it should NOT contain client classes\n543: ```\n544: \n545: #### SCENARIO-062: Clients submodule exports ControlPlaneClient\n546: ```gherkin\n547: GIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\n548: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is imported\n549: THEN it should be available\n550: ```\n551: \n552: #### SCENARIO-063: Clients submodule exports CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n553: ```gherkin\n554: GIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\n555: WHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is imported\n556: THEN it should be available\n557: ```\n558: \n559: #### SCENARIO-064: Clients submodule exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n560: ```gherkin\n561: GIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\n562: WHEN AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is imported\n563: THEN it should be available\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ---\n567: \n568: ### REQ-009: Integration tests for end-to-end flows\n569: \n570: #### SCENARIO-065: CodeInterpreterClient full lifecycle\n571: ```gherkin\n572: GIVEN a test environment with mocked Workload Manager and Router endpoints\n573: WHEN the following code executes:\n574:   with CodeInterpreterClient(\n575:       name=\"test-int\",\n576:       namespace=\"test-ns\",\n577:       workload_manager_url=\"http://wm-mock\",\n578:       router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n579:   ) as client:\n580:       result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'integration test'\")\n581: THEN POST to Workload Manager should create a session\n582: AND Data plane client should be initialized with the session ID\n583: AND execute_command should return the expected output\n584: AND DELETE to Workload Manager should clean up the session on exit\n585: ```\n586: \n587: #### SCENARIO-066: AgentRuntimeClient invoke flow\n588: ```gherkin\n589: GIVEN a test environment with mocked Router endpoint\n590: WHEN the following code executes:\n591:   with AgentRuntimeClient(\n592:       agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n593:       namespace=\"test-ns\",\n594:       router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n595:   ) as client:\n596:       response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n597: THEN GET request should bootstrap the session ID\n598: AND POST request should invoke the agent with the payload\n599: AND Context manager should close the HTTP session\n600: ```\n601: \n602: ---\n603: \n604: ### REQ-010: Environment variable resolution tests\n605: \n606: #### SCENARIO-067: Workload Manager URL from environment\n607: ```gherkin\n608: GIVEN WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://wm-env\" environment variable set\n609: AND no workload_manager_url argument\n610: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n611: THEN base_url should be \"http://wm-env\"\n612: ```\n613: \n614: #### SCENARIO-068: Router URL from environment\n615: ```gherkin\n616: GIVEN ROUTER_URL=\"http://router-env\" environment variable set\n617: AND no router_url argument\n618: WHEN CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n619: THEN router_url should be \"http://router-env\"\n620: ```\n621: \n622: #### SCENARIO-069: Auth token from SA file\n623: ```gherkin\n624: GIVEN no auth_token argument\n625: AND SA token file at /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token contains \"sa-token\"\n626: WHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n627: THEN auth_token should be \"sa-token\"\n628: ```\n629: \n630: ---\n631: \n632: ### REQ-011: Timeout behavior tests\n633: \n634: #### SCENARIO-070: Control plane timeout defaults\n635: ```gherkin\n636: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient without timeout arguments\n637: WHEN a request is made\n638: THEN timeout should be (5.0, 120)\n639: ```\n640: \n641: #### SCENARIO-071: Control plane timeout override\n642: ```gherkin\n643: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0\n644: WHEN a request is made\n645: THEN timeout should be (3.0, 60)\n646: ```\n647: \n648: #### SCENARIO-072: CodeInterpreterClient timeout defaults\n649: ```gherkin\n650: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient without timeout arguments\n651: WHEN a data plane operation is performed\n652: THEN timeout should be (5.0, 120)\n653: ```\n654: \n655: #### SCENARIO-073: CodeInterpreterClient timeout override\n656: ```gherkin\n657: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with timeout=90, connect_timeout=4.0\n658: WHEN a data plane operation is performed\n659: THEN timeout should be (4.0, 90)\n660: ```\n661: \n662: ---\n663: \n664: ### REQ-012: HTTP connection pooling tests\n665: \n666: #### SCENARIO-074: ControlPlaneClient uses pooled session\n667: ```gherkin\n668: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient\n669: WHEN the HTTP session is inspected\n670: THEN pool_connections should be 10\n671: AND pool_maxsize should be 10\n672: ```\n673: \n674: #### SCENARIO-075: DataPlaneClient uses pooled session\n675: ```gherkin\n676: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n677: WHEN the HTTP session is inspected\n678: THEN pool_connections should be 10\n679: AND pool_maxsize should be 10\n680: ```\n681: \n682: #### SCENARIO-076: Custom pool configuration\n683: ```gherkin\n684: GIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=30\n685: WHEN the HTTP session is inspected\n686: THEN pool_connections should be 20\n687: AND pool_maxsize should be 30\n688: ```\n689: \n690: ---\n691: \n692: ### REQ-013: Session header management tests\n693: \n694: #### SCENARIO-077: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient sets session header\n695: ```gherkin\n696: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\n697: WHEN _request is called\n698: THEN the request should include \"x-agentcube-session-id: test-session\" header\n699: ```\n700: \n701: #### SCENARIO-078: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient uses SESSION_HEADER constant\n702: ```gherkin\n703: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n704: WHEN a request is made\n705: THEN the session header name should be from SESSION_HEADER constant\n706: ```\n707: \n708: ---\n709: \n710: ### REQ-014: Error handling tests\n711: \n712: #### SCENARIO-079: Request timeout handled\n713: ```gherkin\n714: GIVEN a client and a request that times out\n715: WHEN the request is made\n716: THEN requests.Timeout should be handled appropriately\n717: ```\n718: \n719: #### SCENARIO-080: Connection error handled\n720: ```gherkin\n721: GIVEN a client and a connection failure\n722: WHEN the request is made\n723: THEN requests.ConnectionError should be handled appropriately\n724: ```\n725: \n726: #### SCENARIO-081: HTTP error handled\n727: ```gherkin\n728: GIVEN a client and a 500 response\n729: WHEN the request is made\n730: THEN the error should be logged or raised appropriately\n731: ```\n732: \n733: ---\n734: \n735: ### REQ-015: Logger tests\n736: \n737: #### SCENARIO-082: Client creates logger\n738: ```gherkin\n739: GIVEN a client with verbose=True\n740: WHEN the client is initialized\n741: THEN a logger should be created\n742: AND the logger level should be appropriate for verbose mode\n743: ```\n744: \n745: #### SCENARIO-083: Client uses logger for operations\n746: ```gherkin\n747: GIVEN a client with verbose=True\n748: WHEN an operation is performed\n749: THEN the operation should be logged\n750: ```\n751: \n752: ---\n753: \n754: ## Test Structure\n755: \n756: Tests should be organized as:\n757: - `tests/test_control_plane.py` — ControlPlaneClient tests\n758: - `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests\n759: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests\n760: - `tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` — CodeInterpreterClient tests\n761: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` — AgentRuntimeClient tests\n762: - `tests/test_utils.py` — Utility function tests\n763: - `tests/test_exceptions.py` — Exception class tests\n764: - `tests/test_integration.py` — Integration tests\n765: \n766: ## Test Framework\n767: \n768: - Use `pytest` as the test framework\n769: - Use `responses` or `httpx_mock` for HTTP request mocking\n770: - Use `pytest-mock` for mocking objects\n771: - Use `pytest-cov` for coverage reporting\n772: \n773: ## Coverage Goals\n774: \n775: - Unit test coverage: >80% for all SDK modules\n776: - Integration test coverage: Key end-to-end flows\n777: - Edge cases and error paths should be covered\n\n(End of file - total 777 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `sdk-python/tests`\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\nTask: Add comprehensive unit tests for AgentCube Python SDK components\n\n## Base Specs\n\n- `python-sdk/design.md` — Package layout, client APIs, configuration, HTTP contracts\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` — SDK requirements with acceptance scenarios\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Unit tests for ControlPlaneClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: Create session success\n```gherkin","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775899604875,"end":1775899604900}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899604917,"sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdd752b001z4s6F1RqEvh4Vz","messageID":"msg_d7bdd641c001Opu8y7C8PcjL9A","sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f2bbac573ff34e9eb4ab8c6fb03f8a5a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n10: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Version display\n13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n14: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n18: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n19: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n20: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n21: \n22: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n26: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n27: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n36: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n37: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `build` command\n41: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n45: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n46: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n49: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n50: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n54: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n55: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n59: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n62: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n63: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n66: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n67: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n71: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n72: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n76: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n79: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n80: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n83: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n84: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n88: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n89: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n93: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n94: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n95: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: `status` command\n98: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n101: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n102: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Not published\n105: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n106: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n110: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n113: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n118: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n119: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n123: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Save location\n126: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n127: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n128: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n131: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n132: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n133: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n136: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n140: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Push image\n144: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n145: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Remove image\n149: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n150: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n154: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n157: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n158: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n162: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n163: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n167: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n168: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n175: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n176: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n180: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n183: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n184: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n185: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n188: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n191: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n192: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n193: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n#### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md","time":{"start":1775899604879,"end":1775899604915}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899604920,"sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdd7778001WwO1ilOaP0v7jI","messageID":"msg_d7bdd641c001Opu8y7C8PcjL9A","sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ac958fa347124a6098a633adc4f4476d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Integrations Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n10: \n11: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n16: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n17: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n22: \n23: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n28: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n29: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n34: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n35: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n46: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n47: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n52: \n53: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n58: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n59: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n64: \n65: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n70: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n71: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n76: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n82: \n83: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n88: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n89: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n94: \n95: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n100: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n101: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n106: \n107: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n112: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n113: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n118: \n119: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n124: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n125: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n130: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n131: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n136: \n137: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n142: - **WHEN** the service starts\n143: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n148: \n149: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n154: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n155: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n160: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n161: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n166: \n167: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n172: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n173: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n178: \n179: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n184: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n185: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n190: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n191: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Integrations Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nNormative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n- **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md","time":{"start":1775899604881,"end":1775899604918}}}}
