{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899694217,"sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bded3b4001EHAEbIq72ZffWy","messageID":"msg_d7bddcf29001reCNewZhVNIFco","sessionID":"ses_28422b2f4ffeXengGc1bktmjnF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-52a9eea77ab4493b89ed3774c2271355","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# delta-spec: AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `docs`\nLanguage: Markdown\nTask: Create comprehensive architecture design documentation and API documentation for AgentCube platform\n\n## Base Specs\n\n- `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` — System architecture overview\n- `docs/docs/api/overview.md` — API overview and reference\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Architecture overview documentation completeness\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: Architecture overview includes system components\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reads the overview section\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include all core components: Router, Store, Workload Manager, PicoD, and their relationships\nAND each component SHALL have a clear description of its purpose and functionality\nAND component interactions SHALL be documented with diagrams\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-002: Architecture overview includes data flow diagrams\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews the data flow section\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include sequence diagrams showing request flow\nAND session lifecycle SHALL be documented with state diagrams\nAND all critical paths SHALL be visualized using Mermaid diagrams\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-003: Architecture overview includes security architecture\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture overview documentation\nWHEN a security engineer reviews the security section\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe multi-layer security mechanisms\nAND network security measures SHALL be documented (TLS, NetworkPolicy)\nAND authentication and authorization SHALL be detailed (JWT, RBAC)\nAND resource isolation SHALL be explained (Pod, Namespace)\nAND resource limits SHALL be specified\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-004: Architecture overview includes scalability design\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture overview documentation\nWHEN a system architect reviews the scalability section\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe horizontal scaling strategies\nAND vertical scaling approaches SHALL be documented\nAND load balancing architecture SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-005: Architecture overview includes monitoring and observability\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture overview documentation\nWHEN a DevOps engineer reviews the monitoring section\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe monitoring architecture\nAND core metrics SHALL be defined\nAND logging and tracing SHALL be documented\nAND integration with Prometheus, Loki, and Jaeger SHALL be explained\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Architecture modules documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-006: Modules documentation describes each component\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the architecture modules documentation\nWHEN a developer reads about a specific component\nTHEN each module SHALL have detailed documentation\nAND the documentation SHALL include: purpose, responsibilities, interfaces, and dependencies\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-007: Router module documentation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the Router module documentation\nWHEN a developer reads it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe Router's role as the entry point\nAND request routing logic SHALL be explained\nAND session management SHALL be detailed\nAND authentication middleware SHALL be documented\nAND rate limiting SHALL be described\nAND health checks SHALL be specified\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-008: Store module documentation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the Store module documentation\nWHEN a developer reads it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe session data storage\nAND caching mechanisms SHALL be explained\nAND data persistence SHALL be documented\nAND distributed locking SHALL be described\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-009: Workload Manager module documentation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the Workload Manager module documentation\nWHEN a developer reads it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe Kubernetes resource management\nAND AgentRuntime resource handling SHALL be documented\nAND CodeInterpreter resource handling SHALL be documented\nAND Pod lifecycle management SHALL be explained\nAND resource quota control SHALL be specified\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-010: PicoD module documentation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the PicoD module documentation\nWHEN a developer reads it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe code execution environment\nAND file operations SHALL be documented\nAND workspace management SHALL be explained\nAND status reporting SHALL be described\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Data flow documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-011: Data flow documentation includes request processing\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the data flow documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews request processing\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include detailed sequence diagrams\nAND each step SHALL be explained\nAND component interactions SHALL be clear\nAND response paths SHALL be documented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-012: Data flow documentation includes session lifecycle\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the data flow documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews session lifecycle\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include all session states\nAND state transitions SHALL be documented\nAND timeouts and expiration SHALL be explained\nAND cleanup processes SHALL be described\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-013: Data flow documentation includes error handling\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the data flow documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews error handling\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe error propagation\nAND retry mechanisms SHALL be documented\nAND fallback strategies SHALL be explained\nAND error codes SHALL be defined\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: API documentation overview\n\n#### SCENARIO-014: API overview includes version information\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reads it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL specify the current API version\nAND versioning strategy SHALL be explained\nAND backward compatibility SHALL be documented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-015: API overview includes authentication\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews authentication\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe JWT token usage\nAND token acquisition SHALL be documented with examples\nAND token usage in requests SHALL be explained\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-016: API overview includes response formats\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews response formats\nTHEN the documentation SHALL specify success response format\nAND error response format SHALL be documented\nAND common fields SHALL be explained\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-017: API overview includes error codes\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API overview documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews error codes\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all error codes\nAND HTTP status codes SHALL be mapped to error codes\nAND error descriptions SHALL be provided\nAND resolution hints SHALL be included\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Session management API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-018: Session creation API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the session management API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews session creation\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND request parameters SHALL be documented with types and descriptions\nAND request body schema SHALL be provided\nAND response schema SHALL be documented\nAND example requests and responses SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-019: Session query API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the session management API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews session query\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND path parameters SHALL be documented\nAND response schema SHALL be provided\nAND example responses SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-020: Session list API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the session management API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews session listing\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND query parameters SHALL be documented with filters\nAND pagination SHALL be explained\nAND response schema SHALL be provided\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-021: Session deletion API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the session management API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews session deletion\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND response schema SHALL be documented\nAND cleanup behavior SHALL be explained\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Resource proxy API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-022: AgentRuntime proxy API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the resource proxy API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews AgentRuntime proxy\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include the proxy endpoint pattern\nAND required headers SHALL be documented (Authorization, Session-ID)\nAND request methods SHALL be explained\nAND response behavior SHALL be described\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-023: CodeInterpreter proxy API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the resource proxy API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews CodeInterpreter proxy\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include the proxy endpoint pattern\nAND required headers SHALL be documented\nAND request methods SHALL be explained\nAND response behavior SHALL be described\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Code execution API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-024: Code execution API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the code execution API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews code execution\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND required headers SHALL be documented\nAND request body schema SHALL be provided (code, language, timeout, working_dir)\nAND response schema SHALL be documented (stdout, stderr, exit_code, duration)\nAND example requests and responses SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-025: Language support documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the code execution API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews language support\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all supported languages\nAND language-specific features SHALL be explained\nAND limitations SHALL be documented\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: File operations API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-026: File upload API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the file operations API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews file upload\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND required headers SHALL be documented\nAND form fields SHALL be documented (file, path, mode)\nAND response schema SHALL be provided\nAND example requests and responses SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-027: File list API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the file operations API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews file listing\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND query parameters SHALL be documented\nAND response schema SHALL be provided\nAND example responses SHALL be included\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-028: File download API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the file operations API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews file download\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND required headers SHALL be documented\nAND response behavior SHALL be explained\nAND error handling SHALL be documented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-029: File deletion API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the file operations API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews file deletion\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND response schema SHALL be documented\nAND error handling SHALL be explained\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Health check API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-030: Liveness probe API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the health check API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews liveness probe\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND response schema SHALL be documented\nAND probe behavior SHALL be explained\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-031: Readiness probe API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the health check API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews readiness probe\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include endpoint path and method\nAND response schema SHALL be documented\nAND component status SHALL be explained\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Rate limiting documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-032: Rate limiting rules documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews rate limiting\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all rate limiting rules\nAND limits SHALL be specified for each type\nAND time windows SHALL be defined\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-033: Rate limiting response documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews rate limiting responses\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe the 429 response\nAND retry-after header SHALL be documented\nAND client behavior SHALL be recommended\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: SDK API documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-034: Python SDK API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews Python SDK\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all public classes and methods\nAND method signatures SHALL be documented\nAND parameter types SHALL be specified\nAND return types SHALL be documented\nAND example code SHALL be provided\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-035: Go Client API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews Go Client\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all public types and methods\nAND method signatures SHALL be documented\nAND parameter types SHALL be specified\nAND return types SHALL be documented\nAND example code SHALL be provided\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-036: JavaScript SDK API documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer reviews JavaScript SDK\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list all public classes and methods\nAND method signatures SHALL be documented\nAND parameter types SHALL be specified\nAND return types SHALL be documented\nAND example code SHALL be provided\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: API examples and tutorials\n\n#### SCENARIO-037: Complete workflow examples provided\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer looks for examples\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include complete workflow examples\nAND examples SHALL cover common use cases\nAND each example SHALL include all necessary steps\nAND code SHALL be executable\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-038: Code interpreter tutorial provided\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer learns about code interpreter\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include a step-by-step tutorial\nAND tutorial SHALL cover session creation, code execution, and file operations\nAND tutorial SHALL be easy to follow\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-039: Agent runtime tutorial provided\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN a developer learns about agent runtime\nTHEN the documentation SHALL include a step-by-step tutorial\nAND tutorial SHALL cover session bootstrap and agent invocation\nAND tutorial SHALL be easy to follow\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: Documentation quality standards\n\n#### SCENARIO-040: All diagrams are valid Mermaid\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the documentation\nWHEN diagrams are rendered\nTHEN all Mermaid diagrams SHALL be valid syntax\nAND diagrams SHALL render correctly\nAND diagrams SHALL be clearly labeled\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-041: All code examples are tested\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the documentation\nWHEN code examples are executed\nTHEN all examples SHALL be syntactically correct\nAND examples SHALL use valid API endpoints\nAND examples SHALL produce expected results\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-042: All API endpoints are documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the API documentation\nWHEN all endpoints are reviewed\nTHEN every public API endpoint SHALL be documented\nAND each endpoint SHALL have a complete description\nAND each endpoint SHALL have examples\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-043: Cross-references are accurate\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the documentation\nWHEN cross-references are followed\nTHEN all internal links SHALL be valid\nAND cross-references SHALL point to relevant sections\nAND related concepts SHALL be linked\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Deployment architecture documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-044: Kubernetes deployment documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the deployment architecture documentation\nWHEN a DevOps engineer reviews it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe Kubernetes deployment strategy\nAND required resources SHALL be specified\nAND configuration options SHALL be documented\nAND scaling recommendations SHALL be provided\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-045: High availability architecture documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the deployment architecture documentation\nWHEN a system architect reviews it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe HA architecture\nAND failure recovery mechanisms SHALL be documented\nAND disaster recovery strategies SHALL be explained\nAND multi-cluster deployment SHALL be described\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: Security documentation\n\n#### SCENARIO-046: Security best practices documented\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the security documentation\nWHEN a security engineer reviews it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL list security best practices\nAND common vulnerabilities SHALL be addressed\nAND mitigation strategies SHALL be provided\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-047: Compliance documentation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the security documentation\nWHEN a compliance officer reviews it\nTHEN the documentation SHALL describe security controls\nAND audit capabilities SHALL be documented\nAND compliance standards SHALL be referenced\n```\n\n---\n\n## Documentation Structure\n\nDocumentation should be organized as:\n- `docs/docs/architecture/` — Architecture documentation\n  - `overview.md` — System architecture overview\n  - `modules.md` — Component module documentation\n  - `data-flow.md` — Data flow and sequence diagrams\n  - `security.md` — Security architecture\n  - `scalability.md` — Scalability design\n  - `monitoring.md` — Monitoring and observability\n- `docs/docs/api/` — API documentation\n  - `overview.md` — API overview and reference\n  - `sessions.md` — Session management API\n  - `proxy.md` — Resource proxy API\n  - `execution.md` — Code execution API\n  - `files.md` — File operations API\n  - `health.md` — Health check API\n  - `sdk/` — SDK documentation\n    - `python.md` — Python SDK\n    - `go.md` — Go Client\n    - `javascript.md` — JavaScript SDK\n- `docs/docs/deployment/` — Deployment documentation\n  - `overview.md` — Deployment overview\n  - `kubernetes.md` — Kubernetes deployment\n  - `security.md` — Security configuration\n\n## Documentation Quality Metrics\n\n- All architecture diagrams shall be valid Mermaid syntax\n- All API endpoints shall have complete documentation\n- All code examples shall be tested and executable\n- All cross-references shall be valid\n- Documentation shall be reviewed by at least two team members\n- Documentation shall be updated with each release\n- Documentation shall include troubleshooting guides\n- Documentation shall include migration guides for API changes","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775899694082,"end":1775899694214}}}}
